# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldMage3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had spend most of her day in deep thought."
    new "Sarah had spend most of her day in deep thought."

    old "When even the sun had begun to set, and she was no closer to an answer, she had taken to wandering the house."
    new "When even the sun had begun to set, and she was no closer to an answer, she had taken to wandering the house."

    old "She had spend years in this house, and over the course of it, she had come to know it like a maze."
    new "She had spend years in this house, and over the course of it, she had come to know it like a maze."

    old "No, she thought."
    new "No, she thought."

    old "Not quite a maze, for a maze could be mastered and understood."
    new "Not quite a maze, for a maze could be mastered and understood."

    old "The house, rather, was forever changing and resisting being understood."
    new "The house, rather, was forever changing and resisting being understood."

    old "Rooms would be where they were. Only until they were not."
    new "Rooms would be where they were. Only until they were not."

    old "Hallways would have an exact number of doors. Only until it had more."
    new "Hallways would have an exact number of doors. Only until it had more."

    old "In the first year, Sarah had dedicated significant amounts of her intellect on trying to solve the puzzle that was the house."
    new "In the first year, Sarah had dedicated significant amounts of her intellect on trying to solve the puzzle that was the house."

    old "Only when Xan had told her to give up on it, did she finally relent and accept that the house was beyond her ability to grasp."
    new "Only when Xan had told her to give up on it, did she finally relent and accept that the house was beyond her ability to grasp."

    old "Still, on occasion, she could not resist pondering the mystery."
    new "Still, on occasion, she could not resist pondering the mystery."

    old "It was near the end of the night that Sarah came upon a room she had not yet encountered before."
    new "It was near the end of the night that Sarah came upon a room she had not yet encountered before."

    old "The room appeared lived."
    new "The room appeared lived."

    old "Exploring through its contents, she found more relics, more writing and more books. Always more books."
    new "Exploring through its contents, she found more relics, more writing and more books. Always more books."

    old "Looking at the table, she saw a familiar handwriting covering the papers."
    new "Looking at the table, she saw a familiar handwriting covering the papers."

    old "Aah, I see you've come upon his private study."
    new "Aah, I see you've come upon his private study."

    old "Sarah felt her brow furrow."
    new "Sarah felt her brow furrow."

    old "I thought you would have been up to something else by now."
    new "I thought you would have been up to something else by now."

    old "Or did you really work so hard to rid yourself of Xan just so you could torture me?"
    new "Or did you really work so hard to rid yourself of Xan just so you could torture me?"

    old "It's a lonely house."
    new "It's a lonely house."

    old "Either I torture you, or I torture your new friend."
    new "Either I torture you, or I torture your new friend."

    old "Sarah snapped towards the spirit."
    new "Sarah snapped towards the spirit."

    old "You leave her alone, got that?"
    new "You leave her alone, got that?"

    old "Only jest. We are all friends here."
    new "Only jest. We are all friends here."

    old "What else is there for me to do?"
    new "What else is there for me to do?"

    old "Sarah ignored the spirit's pleading."
    new "Sarah ignored the spirit's pleading."

    old "Did you say this was Xan's private study?"
    new "Did you say this was Xan's private study?"

    old "Yes. He was a man who enjoyed his secrets."
    new "Yes. He was a man who enjoyed his secrets."

    old "Then how did you know about this place?"
    new "Then how did you know about this place?"

    old "The spirit swirled around, exploring the corners of the room."
    new "The spirit swirled around, exploring the corners of the room."

    old "He knew you had sympathies for me, and so he carried out his interrogations with me in this place."
    new "He knew you had sympathies for me, and so he carried out his interrogations with me in this place."

    old "interrogations."
    new "interrogations."

    old "Tortures, to be more exact."
    new "Tortures, to be more exact."

    old "His magic...your magic. To my kind it feels as flesh pressed against a forge."
    new "His magic...your magic. To my kind it feels as flesh pressed against a forge."

    old "Sarah shivered at the idea."
    new "Sarah shivered at the idea."

    old "I never knew..."
    new "I never knew..."

    old "He did not want you to know, and I did not want to burden you with such knowledge."
    new "He did not want you to know, and I did not want to burden you with such knowledge."

    old "Burden me? It was you who he tortured. I would have listened to you..."
    new "Burden me? It was you who he tortured. I would have listened to you..."

    old "I know you would have, child."
    new "I know you would have, child."

    old "You would have listened, and cared and you would have pleaded for him to stop."
    new "You would have listened, and cared and you would have pleaded for him to stop."

    old "But your heart is soft while his was made of iron."
    new "But your heart is soft while his was made of iron."

    old "He would have continued the tortures, and back then, you would have been too weak to stop him."
    new "He would have continued the tortures, and back then, you would have been too weak to stop him."

    old "And you would have been eaten by the guilt of serving a master so wicked."
    new "And you would have been eaten by the guilt of serving a master so wicked."

    old "I wanted to spare you such troubles, and so I kept it a secret."
    new "I wanted to spare you such troubles, and so I kept it a secret."

    old "Sarah felt a deep sadness in her heart, knowing that all these years, she had not even realized this horror."
    new "Sarah felt a deep sadness in her heart, knowing that all these years, she had not even realized this horror."

    old "And the spirit, for all that it was, appeared not deserving of such brutality."
    new "And the spirit, for all that it was, appeared not deserving of such brutality."

    old "Does this place make you sad?"
    new "Does this place make you sad?"

    old "The spirit twirled around in the room for a while. Observing it."
    new "The spirit twirled around in the room for a while. Observing it."

    old "It doesn't make me feel much of anything."
    new "It doesn't make me feel much of anything."

    old "It doesn't scare you? It would scare me."
    new "It doesn't scare you? It would scare me."

    old "His tortures were cruel, but he never drew anything from me that mattered, and so I know in the end he only stained his own soul with his crimes."
    new "His tortures were cruel, but he never drew anything from me that mattered, and so I know in the end he only stained his own soul with his crimes."

    old "Best to forgive and move on."
    new "Best to forgive and move on."

    old "Now that he is dead?"
    new "Now that he is dead?"

    old "Sarah sighed and leaned back over the desk."
    new "Sarah sighed and leaned back over the desk."

    old "She reached down and grabbed a book that laid atop all the others."
    new "She reached down and grabbed a book that laid atop all the others."

    old "Sarah read the title."
    new "Sarah read the title."

    old "'The Hollow World'."
    new "'The Hollow World'."

    old "The tome appeared thick and heavy. The leather binding expensive."
    new "The tome appeared thick and heavy. The leather binding expensive."

    old "Sarah held it in her hand and look up towards Razaphel who spun around like a child through the air."
    new "Sarah held it in her hand and look up towards Razaphel who spun around like a child through the air."

    old "Do you have any idea what Xan was working on in here?"
    new "Do you have any idea what Xan was working on in here?"

    old "Nothing I could ever be sure of. Whenever he brought me here, it was he who was asking me the questions."
    new "Nothing I could ever be sure of. Whenever he brought me here, it was he who was asking me the questions."

    old "She held up the book to him."
    new "She held up the book to him."

    old "Do you know what this is?"
    new "Do you know what this is?"

    old "I do, but child, you told me you longed to be free."
    new "I do, but child, you told me you longed to be free."

    old "It is a waste for a girl of your age to spend her time with dusty old books."
    new "It is a waste for a girl of your age to spend her time with dusty old books."

    old "Sarah continued to hold up the book towards the spirit."
    new "Sarah continued to hold up the book towards the spirit."

    old "I thought we were done playing tricks and riddles. Tell me what this book is."
    new "I thought we were done playing tricks and riddles. Tell me what this book is."

    old "Razaphel slowly descended down, his mask-face pressed close to the cover of the book."
    new "Razaphel slowly descended down, his mask-face pressed close to the cover of the book."

    old "It is the foundational text of their order."
    new "It is the foundational text of their order."

    old "Written about three millenia ago, after the fall of their empire."
    new "Written about three millenia ago, after the fall of their empire."

    old "This book is three thousand years old?"
    new "This book is three thousand years old?"

    old "Sarah struggled to imagine such a thing."
    new "Sarah struggled to imagine such a thing."

    old "No, not this copy. But the text it contains is close enough to the original."
    new "No, not this copy. But the text it contains is close enough to the original."

    old "Perhaps a few minor revisions."
    new "Perhaps a few minor revisions."

    old "Sarah placed the book back down and flipped open the cover."
    new "Sarah placed the book back down and flipped open the cover."

    old "Near the start of it, a long itemized index gave hints to the many pages and chapters it contained."
    new "Near the start of it, a long itemized index gave hints to the many pages and chapters it contained."

    old "What is it about?"
    new "What is it about?"

    old "The spirit produced the hissing laugh. Sarah never felt comfortable when it did."
    new "The spirit produced the hissing laugh. Sarah never felt comfortable when it did."

    old "You want me for me to summarize this text for you? Impossible."
    new "You want me for me to summarize this text for you? Impossible."

    old "So you don't know what it is, after all?"
    new "So you don't know what it is, after all?"

    old "How do you explain the world to a child?"
    new "How do you explain the world to a child?"

    old "Are you calling me stupid?"
    new "Are you calling me stupid?"

    old "The spirit swirled around."
    new "The spirit swirled around."

    old "No, Sarah, I do not believe you are foolish. Rather the opposite."
    new "No, Sarah, I do not believe you are foolish. Rather the opposite."

    old "So what then? What is it about?"
    new "So what then? What is it about?"

    old "The book is a dense work, written in a different age, based upon principles that stretch back even further."
    new "The book is a dense work, written in a different age, based upon principles that stretch back even further."

    old "If I explain it to you, I can only do so as one explains the world to a child."
    new "If I explain it to you, I can only do so as one explains the world to a child."

    old "In analogy. In reduction. In simplicity."
    new "In analogy. In reduction. In simplicity."

    old "But a child does not know the world when we shrink it down for them, they know only the simplified version."
    new "But a child does not know the world when we shrink it down for them, they know only the simplified version."

    old "If you wish to learn of this book, truly learn it, you must commit yourself to the work that proceeds it."
    new "If you wish to learn of this book, truly learn it, you must commit yourself to the work that proceeds it."

    old "To understand this work and what it aims to produce, you must read several volumes that proceed it."
    new "To understand this work and what it aims to produce, you must read several volumes that proceed it."

    old "Sufficiently ground your understanding of the principles at play."
    new "Sufficiently ground your understanding of the principles at play."

    old "There exists no simplified version that would not butcher the truth so as to make it meaningless."
    new "There exists no simplified version that would not butcher the truth so as to make it meaningless."

    old "Sarah stepped back and eyed the book."
    new "Sarah stepped back and eyed the book."

    old "Fine, what do I need to read then?"
    new "Fine, what do I need to read then?"

    old "Always so eager..."
    new "Always so eager..."

    old "I shall prepare a list for you, should you truly be interested."
    new "I shall prepare a list for you, should you truly be interested."

    old "Thank you, Razaphel."
    new "Thank you, Razaphel."

    old "Sarah suddenly felt her body wobble."
    new "Sarah suddenly felt her body wobble."

    old "Only just in time did she grab hold of the back of the chair, keeping herself upright."
    new "Only just in time did she grab hold of the back of the chair, keeping herself upright."

    old "You're tired, child."
    new "You're tired, child."

    old "I think you're right..."
    new "I think you're right..."

    old "You don't need to solve all the world's problems in a day. Go, rest Princess."
    new "You don't need to solve all the world's problems in a day. Go, rest Princess."

    old "Sarah laughed as she moved towards the door."
    new "Sarah laughed as she moved towards the door."

    old "I'm not a princess anymore, Razaphel."
    new "I'm not a princess anymore, Razaphel."

    old "She stumbled through the door. Sarah could not recall how she made her way back to her room, only that she did."
    new "She stumbled through the door. Sarah could not recall how she made her way back to her room, only that she did."

